# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout regardless of platform or the checking-out user's
# core.autocrlf setting. Root-cause fix for a real bug: a CRLF-converted blank line inside an
# embedded HTML asset (src/hub/manage/assets/index.html) collided with the HTTP header/body
# delimiter on hosted Windows CI runners (Git for Windows defaults core.autocrlf=true there),
# deterministically truncating a Console route test. Rust source, embedded web assets, and docs
# must be byte-identical across every checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows batch scripts want CRLF: label/GOTO parsing can misbehave with bare LF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Explicit binaries: never text-normalized, never diffed as text.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
